                "content": "Looking for some input on an acquisition we're evaluating. We're a $14B retail corp and targeting an e-commerce logistics company - they've got about $380M revenue, been growing 22% YoY, positive EBITDA around $45M. Strong warehouse footprint in the midwest and southeast.\n\nThe strategic fit is pretty clear - we need better omnichannel fulfillment and their last-mile capabilities would plug directly into our store network. We're looking at roughly 8x EBITDA which is actually below where comparable deals have traded lately (GXO, Radial acquisitions were at 10-12x).\n\nMain thesis is we can unlock $35-40M in annual synergies within 24 months through consolidated distribution and reduced 3PL spend. What's your read on the logic here?",
