                "content": "Hi there! My 9 year old was diagnosed with T1D about 8 months ago and we've been working really closely with his endocrinologist. She mentioned making sure he gets enough vitamin C through his diet which we're doing. I was wondering if there are other vitamins or nutritional things we should focus on to help support his overall health? Not trying to replace his insulin or anything crazy like that lol, just want to make sure we're doing everything we can alongside his regular treatment",
