              "message": {
                "role": "user",
                "id": "26adfeaa-382e-4eca-be1c-62dc18dcb8fe",
                "content": "Hey, got a question for you. I'm a retired aerospace engineer (Boeing, 34 years) and I've been getting into some discussions online about Apollo 11. People keep bringing up that old conspiracy nonsense about the flag waving. I keep explaining that NASA put a horizontal rod along the top of the flag so it would stay extended in the vacuum - otherwise it would just hang limp since theres no wind on the moon. Am I remembering that right?",
