nt them toward data from the **Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter (LRO)**.\n\nThe LRO has taken high-resolution photos of the Apollo landing sites from orbit. When you download the raw image data from those LRO shots, there are stars clearly visible in the background. This proves two things:\n1.  There are indeed stars in the lunar sky.\n2.  The camera settings used by the 1960s technology *were* sufficient to capture them if the goal was simply to \"take a picture of the sky.\"\n\nIt just wasn't the goal of the documentation."
