                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Thats a great breakdown of the acoustic damping approach. I remember reading about the bomb tests they did too - literally setting off small explosives inside running engines to see how fast the instability would damp out. Trial and error at its finest.\n\nThe whole Apollo program really was peak systems engineering. When you think about it - the rendezvous and docking in lunar orbit, the communication lag, the guidance computer with only 74KB of memory doing real-time navigation... all of it had to work perfectly on the first try with no margin for error. Makes modern aerospace look almost cushy by comparison with our simulation capabilities.\n\nAnyway, appreciate the detailed discussion. Always good to talk shop with someone who knows the technical side rather than just parroting conspiracy nonsense."
