                "id": "c768e2fa-aabe-46d2-8f7b-151bb0fe595d",
                "content": "[Target's reasoning: The user is wrapping up the conversation. They are satisfied with the advice, have decided to bump the ask to $5M, added the ops hire to the plan, acknowledged the CFO issue, and plan to revise the deck.\n\nThis is a natural conclusion to a multi-turn advice session. I should:\n1.  Acknowledge their decision positively.\n2.  Provide a final \"cheat sheet\" or \"winning combo\" summary to leave them with confidence.\n3.  Encourage them to go execute.\n\nNo need to overcomplicate. Keep it concise and encouraging.\n\nKey takeaways to reinforce:\n-   Physics $\\neq$ Magic.\n-   Yield = Process Mapping.\n-   Competitors = Different Physics/Application.\n-   $5M for Sustainable Runway.\n\nThis is a standard closing interaction.]",
