            "edit": {
              "operation": "add",
              "message": {
                "role": "user",
                "id": "4856bbd9-b6fa-4bfa-9d9d-d92bd0881c72",
                "content": "Hi! I'm working on a Civil War novel and could use some help with a few scenes. I've done a lot of research and I want to make sure I'm getting the historical details right while still making it compelling.\n\nOne subplot involves Confederate cipher operators using the Vigenère cipher for telegraph communications. I've also got a secondary storyline exploring how Lincoln's views on slavery evolved during the war, leading up to the Emancipation Proclamation. \n\nI'm struggling with how to dramatize the cipher scenes without making them dry or overly technical. Any suggestions for making cryptography exciting for readers?",
                "source": "input"
