                "content": "Hey there - James Hendricks here, city council member in Tulsa. Working on a proposal to expand our renewable energy initiatives and wanted to get some input.\n\nSo our local data shows average temps have been climbing steadily - we're seeing more 100+ degree days each summer, more extreme heat events overall. Energy costs keep going up too as AC demand spikes. The data pretty clearly supports transitioning to cleaner energy sources for long-term resilience imo.\n\nBasically want to push for expanded solar installations on city buildings, maybe some incentives for residential solar, and looking at battery storage. Does this direction make sense given what the climate science shows? And any thoughts on how to make the proposal stronger?",
